verse = \lyricmode {
  He o -- pened out his mouth when foes had come
to fall like hail on the heads of a flock,
The text \"yet did He call on Father's aid—\" only has 8 natural syllables:
heard his ac -- cu -- sers.
He was op -- pressed, and there the Lord re -- lieved him
from all the force that long had seized
as well from God be -- cause man -- kind had grieved him
with all that evil nature used.
}
